summary:
Currently I am the (Interim) Conference Manager at ELIA and started my career in producing TV-shows. I have experience in producing webinars, livestreams, corporate IT conferences and networking events for a C-level networking organisation, but was missing the connection to my passion, the arts. 

With a BA in International Tourism Management and having lived in both London and Cape Town, I have a a strong interest in working with different cultures. I finished my studies with a thesis in sustainability policy development and implementation for tourism organisations. I have a background in hospitality and am at the intersection of culture, arts and tourism, but grew up in a family of writers, musicians and forward thinkers.
